<br>
How so? I assume the original poster meant chain casting pets since he alluded to burnout leggings. How do you chain cast pets vs a summoning mob? In my experience, it's too hard to hit /pet get lost exactly as the casting meter hits 0. I usually end up with the multiple pet message. If you hit /pet get lost too soon you get summoned and your next pet is interrupted.<br>
<br>
I assume the trick is to expend the mob's summon reload on the pet with use of /pet back off. Risky, challenging, death defying. That, or cast from melee range so you're not summoned... but then you're tanking for the entire duration of the spell &gt;&lt;<br>
<br>
